# Basic Terraform workflow

1️⃣ Root Module
   └─ Provides input values to a module
      e.g., module "alb" {
              vpc_id = module.network.vpc_id
              certificate_arn = module.acm.regional_cert_arn
            }

2️⃣ Module Variables (`variables.tf`)
   └─ Declare placeholders for expected inputs
      e.g., variable "vpc_id" { type = string }
            variable "certificate_arn" { type = string }

3️⃣ Module main.tf (Resource Creation)
   └─ Use variables to create AWS resources
      e.g., 
      resource "aws_lb_listener" "https" {
          load_balancer_arn = var.alb_arn
          port              = 443
          protocol          = "HTTPS"
          certificate_arn   = var.certificate_arn
      }
   - **Left side** = Terraform AWS resource arguments (predefined keywords)
   - **Right side** = values from module variables, other resources, or literals

4️⃣ Optional Module Outputs (`outputs.tf`)
   └─ Expose useful values for other modules or root
      e.g., 
      output "alb_arn" {
          value = aws_lb.this.arn
      }

5️⃣ AWS API
   └─ Terraform uses the provider to send the resource arguments and values to AWS
      → Creates ALB, Listener, S3 Bucket, etc.



